snippet.textDisplay:
That's not a plot hole. That's what's called an "outer goal" vs an "inner goal" in writing. In other words, Sonic is a "liar".
While his outer goal was to get the item, his inner goal was to form a connection.
That's why he used the whole thing as an excuse to meet the guy he was spying on and befriending him before leaving earth (something he didn't wanna do anyway) he thought that was his last chance.

I'm surpised people are still missing this point considering they spent so much time on this topic in the movie.

snippet.textDisplay:
The thing I'm mostly complaining about with my friends is why they needed the comedy lift scene inside the building.

I remember the Sonic OVA.

I remember Sonic bouncing/homing in around the sides of a tall skyscraper to stand at the top and look around.

WHY DIDN'T HE JUST DO THAT WHEN HE KNEW WHAT BUILDING IT WAS IN THIS FILM??

We didn't need the confusion of a human casually carrying a 35KG hedgehog in a bag with no problems, because that is heavier than you think.
